Mood quality vs Reported stress

Author

Santiago Sotelo

Published

April 3, 2023

Problem

We need to verify if the variables mood_quality_pre & mood_quality_post in the database have any information and if that information is related to reported_stress_pre & reported_stress_post.

Data

In this report we are using the following databases that conform the dynamic data (MM):

  1. Am data downloaded from microserver
  2. Wildflowers database currently inactive
  3. Actify database currently inactive
  4. Lost data from China, also Am data

A couple of considerations:

  • Wildflowers, Actify, and China Recovery have a problem in the mood quality variables being the case that the values need to be inverted (for example 20% is actually 80%). This fixing process is present in the LCC functions.
  • Wildflowers and Actify donâ€™t have reported_stress_ pre or reported_stress_post variable. So for compatibility reasons, in the LCC functions we rename the mood_quality variables to reported_stress variables.
  • In the case of CN recovery data, mood_quality variables are dropped and we only use reported_stress variables.

Am data (microserver)

China Recovery (CN)

In the case of the Lost data from China, this data has the same format of AmDTx data. Also, we have reported_stress variables and mood_quality variables.

In the case of the variables regarding mood quality, we can see that there are as much as 3 observations that are between 0,1. Also this observations are the same as their reported_stress.

We can group the values in the following frequency table:

Pre
Post

Conclusion

In Am data, mood_quality doesnâ€™t have any useful information (-1, left_blank).

In Wildflowers (WF) & Actify (Ac), since the LCC functions, we renamed the mood_quality variables as reported_stress variables.

In CN Recovery data, since LCC functions, we drop the mood_quality variables. These dropped variables only have as much as 3 observations that are the same as reported_stress.

In conclusion, the mood quality variables are not adding value to the database so in that sense should no longer be supported.
